        "description": "<p><em>Star Wars: Jedi Trials</em> is an educational third person action game where the player takes control of a Padawan learning the ways of the Jedi. At the same time the game teaches science concepts such as simple machines, force, motion, gravity, electricity, simple circuits and magnetism. With some help from Yoda, Anakin Skywalker and others, the player has to stop Count Dooku who is attempting to acquire all pieces of the Sith Holocron.</p>\n<p>Played from a behind view, the young Jedi-in-training moves through the game's 3D levels while fighting different enemies. The force can be used to push, pull and knock out enemies or clear obstacles while the light saber can be used to strike or block fire from blasters. To progress it is also necessary to find holo projectors that contain educational tasks that have to be completed.</p>",
